  <header>
    <h1 class="title">Best Drinks to Keep You Hydrated</h1>
    <img src="https://i.ibb.co/vcfDVjX/Screenshot-2023-12-27-132928.png" alt="Hydration Image" class="responsive-image">
  </header>

  <main>
    <p class="body-text">Staying hydrated is crucial for overall health and vitality. While water remains the ultimate hydrator, several delightful and hydrating beverages offer both refreshment and nourishment. Let's explore some of the top drinks that not only quench your thirst but also provide essential hydration:</p>

    <ol class="drink-list">
      <li>Water: The timeless champion, water, remains the go-to choice for hydration. It's essential for regulating body temperature, aiding digestion, and maintaining overall bodily functions.</li>
      <li>Coconut Water: Packed with electrolytes and potassium, coconut water is a natural hydrator that helps replenish lost fluids, making it an excellent post-workout drink.</li>
      <li>Herbal Teas: Certain herbal teas, like chamomile or mint tea, are hydrating and can contribute to your daily fluid intake. They also offer calming effects and antioxidants.</li>
      <li>Fresh Fruit Juices: Juices from fruits like watermelon, cucumber, and oranges are not only delicious but also hydrating due to their high water content. Plus, they provide essential vitamins and minerals.</li>
      <li>Electrolyte Drinks: Opt for natural or homemade electrolyte drinks, including those with a mix of water, a pinch of salt, and a splash of citrus juice, to replenish electrolytes lost during sweating.</li>
      <li>Infused Water: Elevate your water by infusing it with slices of fruits like lemon, berries, or cucumber, adding a hint of flavor and encouraging increased hydration.</li>
      <li>Milk Alternatives: Unsweetened almond or oat milk can be hydrating and offer a different flavor profile for those seeking alternatives to dairy.</li>
    </ol>

    <p class="note">It's important to note that while these beverages contribute to hydration, moderation is key, especially with drinks containing added sugars or caffeine. Remember, staying adequately hydrated not only boosts energy levels but also supports various bodily functions. Incorporating these hydrating beverages into your routine can help you maintain optimal hydration levels throughout the day, contributing to overall health and well-being. Stay refreshed and nourished!</p>
  </main>

